-- Pakistan Markets to Close for Leader’s Anniversary, Christmas
-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 2012-12-24T04:52:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/pakistan-markets-to-close-for-leader-s-anniversary-christmas.html
Pakistan’s central bank, commercial
banks, stock exchanges and government offices will be closed
tomorrow to commemorate the birth anniversary of Mohammed Ali
Jinnah, the nation’s founder, and Christmas.  The central bank, businesses and government offices will
reopen on Dec. 26, according to the government and the  State
Bank  of Pakistan, the central bank.  The Karachi Stock Exchange will also stay closed tomorrow,
according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
